## 🔑 Key Concept — What is a Process?

Every program running on Linux is called a **process.**
Each process gets a unique ID number called a **PID.**

When an attacker gets into a machine — they run things:
- Reverse shells
- Password crackers
- Keyloggers

These all show up as processes. If you know how to read processes, you can catch attackers in the act.

