## ⌨️ Commands Learned

### Viewing Processes

```bash
ps                        # Show processes in current terminal only
ps aux                    # Show ALL processes on the entire system
top                       # Live dashboard — updates in real time
```

### Filtering Processes

```bash
ps aux | grep "apache"    # Find apache processes specifically
ps aux | grep "/tmp"      # Find anything running from /tmp (red flag)
ps aux | grep "root"      # Show only processes running as root
```

### Sorting by Resource Usage

```bash
ps -aux | sort -rnk 4 | head -10    # Top 10 processes by RAM usage
ps -aux | sort -rnk 3 | head -10    # Top 10 processes by CPU usage
```

### Why `-rnk 4` works:
| Flag | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `-r` | Reverse order (highest first) |
| `-n` | Sort as numbers not text |
| `-k 4` | Sort by column 4 (%MEM) |

