## 📊 Understanding ps aux Columns

```
USER    PID  %CPU  %MEM  COMMAND
albert  3051  1.2  15.4  firefox
```

| Column | Meaning | SOC Relevance |
|---|---|---|
| `USER` | Who is running this process | Root running unknown process = red flag |
| `PID` | Unique process ID number | Use to track or kill a process |
| `%CPU` | CPU usage percentage | Sudden spike = possible malware |
| `%MEM` | RAM usage percentage | High usage from unknown process = suspicious |
| `COMMAND` | Full path and name of program | Wrong path = possible fake/malicious process |

