## 🖥️ Understanding `top`

`top` is like Windows Task Manager — but live.

```
3051  albert  firefox   15.4%RAM  0.7%CPU
2141  albert  gnome-shell  10.7%RAM
```

- Updates automatically every few seconds
- Sorted by CPU usage by default
- Press `q` to quit

**For SOC:** If malware starts running — you see a CPU/RAM spike immediately without running any new command.

