## 🧠 Key Takeaways

1. Every running program is a process — attackers show up here
2. `ps aux` = snapshot of all processes
3. `top` = live dashboard — use during active incidents
4. Always check the FULL PATH not just the process name
5. Anything running from `/tmp/` is suspicious
6. `www-data` running Apache = normal. `root` running Apache from `/tmp/` = malicious
7. Linux kernel processes start with `k` like `kworker` — always normal, ignore them

